HEADWORD: Centrosome
<hw>Cen"tro*some`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ center
+ -<?/ the body.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A peculiar rounded body
lying near the nucleus of a cell. It is regarded as the dynamic element
by means of which the machinery of cell division is organized.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

